<br>
But warriors are not always tanking, especially on raids.  There is 1 MA on the boss so any warrior not offtanking is going to be using high dps low aggro weapons and attacking from the back.  In these situations their DPS will shine and parse much better than a Paladin or SK.<br>
<br>
I know SK get some offensive spells but unless you are using a high delay weapon you are going to lose attacks from the cast.  Add in resists and fizzles and you won't be doing anywhere near what you think your optimal DPS is.<br>
<br>
As a bard I can melee for 80DPS or so, but I can chant dot for 105.  Combine the 2 for 185 ?  I could but then my group would wonder where all their buffs went. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/embarassed.gif ALT=":o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Plus its not realistic.  You will never get optimal numbers.  And forget the pet most places, they are usually more trouble than they are worth.<br>
